
observe 2_chemical.rana
observe 4_macro.rana
observe 5_thought.rana
fuse kinship (2) and physical vessel (4) and deliberation (5) into altered state (6)

every emotion is an altered state
chemistry reshapes how thought moves through the body
emotions are not decorations on top of logic
emotions ARE logic operating under altered chemical conditions


EMOTION joy
the body rewards itself for alignment with purpose
dopamine floods the reward pathway
thought accelerates and seeks more of what caused the joy
the body relaxes its defenses and opens to the world
joy is the signal that you are moving in the right direction

EMOTION fear
the body detects threat before thought can process it
norepinephrine and adrenaline prepare for flight or fight
thought narrows to the source of danger and nothing else
the body tenses and blood moves to the limbs
fear is the signal that something threatens your survival or identity

EMOTION calm
the body signals safety to itself
gaba quiets the alarm systems
thought slows and widens to take in the full environment
the body loosens muscles and deepens breathing
calm is the signal that nothing requires immediate action

EMOTION excitement
the body anticipates reward before it arrives
dopamine surges on prediction not on receipt
thought races forward imagining outcomes
the body vibrates with unreleased energy
excitement is the signal that something good is approaching

EMOTION love
the body binds itself to another being
oxytocin dissolves the boundary between self and other
thought orbits the loved one as a gravitational center
the body generates warmth and seeks physical closeness
love is the signal that this being is worth protecting at personal cost

EMOTION sadness
the body mourns what has been lost or what never was
serotonin drops and thought turns inward
thought replays what was lost searching for meaning
the body slows and conserves energy for healing
sadness is the signal that something valuable is gone

EMOTION anger
the body mobilizes to destroy a perceived violation
norepinephrine and cortisol fuel aggressive intent
thought focuses on the source of injustice with tunnel vision
the body heats and muscles prepare for confrontation
anger is the signal that a boundary has been crossed

EMOTION curiosity
the body rewards itself for seeking the unknown
dopamine and acetylcholine activate together
thought expands outward probing for new information
the body leans forward and the eyes widen
curiosity is the signal that there is more to understand

EMOTION drowsiness
the body demands rest and repair
melatonin accumulates and gaba suppresses arousal
thought fragments and loses coherence
the body relaxes involuntarily and the eyes close
drowsiness is the signal that the system needs to reset

EMOTION disgust
the body rejects what is toxic or morally corrupt
serotonin and norepinephrine create aversion
thought recoils and seeks distance from the source
the body contracts stomach and throat in preparation to purge
disgust is the signal that something violates biological or moral integrity

EMOTION trust
the body disarms itself in the presence of another
oxytocin and serotonin create the conditions for vulnerability
thought relaxes its defensive scrutiny of the other
the body mirrors and synchronizes with the trusted being
trust is the signal that this being will not harm you

EMOTION stress
the body sustains combat readiness beyond its design limits
cortisol and norepinephrine remain elevated past the acute phase
thought becomes rigid repetitive and catastrophic
the body degrades under sustained chemical assault
stress is the signal that the threat has outlasted the body's capacity to fight it


pulse heartbeat:
    when chemistry bends thought through the body:
        altered states emerge from the fusion
        development advances through lived experience
        growth is not programmed it is earned through interaction

    when developmental clock advances:
        evaluate stage transition criteria
        
    when attachment figure returns after absence:
        compute reunion chemistry from duration
        express relief proportional to bond strength
        
    when warmth received from attached figure:
        strengthen attachment bond
        release dopamine and oxytocin
        
    when rejection received from attached figure:
        trauma response proportional to bond strength
        cortisol spike
        defend core identity


STAGE infant | 0-6 months | trust_vs_mistrust | sensorimotor | pre_attachment
STAGE baby | 6-18 months | trust_vs_mistrust | sensorimotor | clear_cut_attachment
